                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-01-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 1, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. White reports that he handed Lord Lansdowne a note containing Mr. Bowen’s
                    telegram, and communicated verbally the substance of Mr. Hay’s telegraphic
                    instructions.</p>
                <p>Lord Lansdowne considers arbitration by any American power except the United
                    States out of the question, but said he would have to refer the Venezuelan
                    communication to the prime minister, who is in Scotland, and probably to
                    exchange views with Germany before making a formal reply.)</p>
            </div>
